      {
        "type": "theory",
        "title": "ðŸ“š Theory: Introduction to Adjectives and Adverbs",
        "content": {
          "introduction": "Adjectives are words that describe nouns: beautiful or good (ber), tall (bor), sweet or tasty (mit), sad (sin). Adverbs are words that describe verbs: quickly (piyo), slowly (mos). In Dholuo, adjectives and adverbs can often be used interchangeably. Thus 'ber' means both 'good' and 'well' and 'piyo' means both 'fast' and 'quickly'.",
          "phrases": [
            {
                "dholuo": "Rach",
                "english": "Bad",
                "notes": "Adjectives may take the particle 'ma' before the word they describe. The particle 'ma' can be translated as 'which is', so 'Chiemo <strong>ma</strong>rach' means 'food which is bad'."
              },
              {
                "dholuo": "Ber", 
                "english": "Good",
                "notes": "Example in sentence: 'Chiemo maber' which means 'food which is good'."
              },
              {
                "dholuo": "Ng'eny", 
                "english": "A lot"
              },
              {
                "dholuo": "Tin", 
                "english": "A little",
                "notes": "Can also mean 'small'"
              },
              {
                "dholuo": "Duong'", 
                "english": "Big"
              },
              {
                "dholuo": "Liet", 
                "english": "Hot",
                "notes": "Example in sentence: 'Chai maliet' which means 'tea which is hot'."
              },
              {
                "dholuo": "Ng'ich", 
                "english": "Cold",
                "notes": "Example in sentence: 'Chai mang'ich' which means 'tea which is cold'."
              },
              {
                "dholuo": "Piyo", 
                "english": "Fast",
                "notes": ""
              },
              {
                "dholuo": "Mos", 
                "english": "Slow",
                "notes": ""
              }
          ],
          "grammar_note": "Let's go over to the next section to see how these adjectives/adverbs are used in a sentence."
        }
      },
